âœ… What is DownwardAPI?
ğŸ‘‰ The downward API allows containers to consume information about themselves or the cluster without using the Kubernetes client or API server.
ğŸ‘‰ It is sometimes useful for a container to have information about itself, without being overly coupled to Kubernetes.
ğŸ‘‰ Example: Suppose you want the Pod's name as an environment variable in the container. DownwardAPI in kubernetes help us to get that information easily.

âœ… How to expose Pod and container fields to a running container?
There are 2 ways:

1ï¸âƒ£ As environment variables
ğŸ‘‰ You can inject the required information as environment variable in the container using the "fieldRef".
ğŸ‘‰ Refer the image for an example.
ğŸ‘‰ You can try it yourself by following the steps provided at https://lnkd.in/gXPzzPzN

2ï¸âƒ£ As files in a downwardAPI volume
ğŸ‘‰ Instead of using environment variables, you can also write the required info into file(s) using the DownwardAPI Volume feature.
ğŸ‘‰ Check the example in the image with this post.
ğŸ‘‰ You can try it yourself by following the steps provided at https://lnkd.in/gefpHsBE

